com.vmware.vcenter.trusted_infrastructure

Interface TrustAuthorityClusters

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService, Service, TrustAuthorityClustersTypes
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    TrustAuthorityClustersStub

    public interface TrustAuthorityClusters
extends Service, TrustAuthorityClustersTypes, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService
    The TrustAuthorityClusters interface manages all the Trust Authority Components on each Trust Authority Host in the cluster. The TrustAuthorityClusters interface transforms a ClusterComputeResource into Trust Authority Cluster and vice versa. This interface was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.

    • Method Detail

      • update

        TrustAuthorityClusters.UpdateInvocation update(java.lang.String cluster,
                                               TrustAuthorityClustersTypes.UpdateSpec spec)
        Updates the state of a cluster. This method was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.

        Operation Errors:
        Error - if there is a generic error.
        NotFound - if spec doesn't match to any cluster compute resource.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.

        Parameters:
        cluster - Cluster id. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: ClusterComputeResource.
        spec - The specification for update of a cluster.
        Returns:
        instance of TrustAuthorityClusters.UpdateInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described update operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.

      • get

        TrustAuthorityClusters.GetInvocation get(java.lang.String cluster)
        Get the result of the last Update operation which matches the cluster id. This method was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.

        Invocation Result:
        The TrustAuthorityClustersTypes.Info instance which contains information about the state of the cluster.

        Operation Errors:
        Error - if there is a generic error.
        NotFound - if cluster doesn't match to any ClusterComputeResource.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have all of the privileges described as follows:

        • Method execution requires TrustedAdmin.ReadTrustedHosts.
        • The resource ClusterComputeResource referenced by the parameter cluster requires System.View.

        Parameters:
        cluster - Cluster id. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: ClusterComputeResource.
        Returns:
        instance of TrustAuthorityClusters.GetInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described get operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.

      • list

        TrustAuthorityClusters.ListInvocation list()
        Returns a list of clusters for this vCenter instance which matches the TrustAuthorityClustersTypes.FilterSpec. This method was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.

        Invocation Result:
        List of TrustAuthorityClustersTypes.Summary for a TrustAuthorityClusters.

        Operation Errors:
        Error - if there is a generic error.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have all of the privileges described as follows:

        • Method execution requires TrustedAdmin.ReadTrustedHosts.
        • The resource ClusterComputeResource referenced by the property TrustAuthorityClustersTypes.FilterSpec.getCluster() requires System.View.

        Returns:
        instance of TrustAuthorityClusters.ListInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described list operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
